### 3. Launch Posts (This Week — Free, High Impact)

These drive the first wave of real users:

**Reddit posts — do all three:**
- `r/webdev` — "I built a free file validator that auto-fixes broken JSON, YAML, CSV and more"
- `r/programming` — same post
- `r/devtools` — same post

**Template:**
```
I got tired of pasting internal configs into random online validators 
so I built FileLint — a free tool that validates and auto-fixes 
JSON, YAML, CSV, Python, SQL, HTML and more.

Drop any file → instant error detection → one-click auto-fix
Privacy-first: files are never stored.

https://filelint.com

Would love feedback!
```

**HackerNews Show HN:**
```
Show HN: FileLint – drag-and-drop file validator with auto-fix (filelint.com)
```

**Product Hunt:**
- Schedule a launch for a Tuesday or Wednesday morning
- These are the highest traffic days

